<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n17104c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n17" href="#n17104c">N17 (VI.B.9)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n17all.htm#n17104c"> 104(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Adam FitzHereford</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">This castle <font color="green">[at Leixlip]</font> is supposed to have been erected in the reign of Henry II. By <mark>Adam de Hereford</mark>, one of the chief followers of Earl Strongbow, from whom he received as a gift the tenement of the Salmon Leap, and other extensive possessions. <small> P., <a name="PENJ" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#PENJ"><cite title="source">The Irish Penny Journal</cite></a> (1840) 114</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
